											<section class="main bio authorbio">
							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/scarlett-buckley/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Scarlett Buckley is a freelance environmental journalist with a passion for learning and exploring. She has a master of science in creative arts and mental health from Queen Mary University of London in England, and her writing has appeared in <em>Earth Island Journal</em>, Sustainable Brands, and Fibre2Fashion. Beyond her writing pursuits, Scarlett embarks on global travels, immersing herself in diverse cultures to draw inspiration for her mission to protect and preserve our planet’s unique ecosystems.</p></div>
												<div class="singlebioimage col nomobile"><img width="520" height="520" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/ScarlettBuckley-520x520.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/ScarlettBuckley-520x520.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/ScarlettBuckley-150x150.jpg 150w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/ScarlettBuckley-768x768.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/ScarlettBuckley-900x900.jpg 900w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/ScarlettBuckley.jpg 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px" /></div>
